author: wn.com
title: Super PAC behind Kasich plans ground blitz in New Hampshire
text: CONCORD, N.H. (AP) â€” A group backing Republican John Kasich's presidential ambitions is sending 40 volunteers from Ohio into New Hampshire this weekend to campaign on his behalf, offering the latest example of how outside money groups are boosting 2016 campaigns. Kasich is betting big that New Hampshire can help propel him toward the Republican presidential nomination. Kasich's campaign has seven staff members on the ground in New Hampshire, and the primary focus at this point in the campaign is on building up leadership teams and key supporters around the state, New Hampshire campaign manager Simon Thomson said. ...
